{"questionId":"13922475","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The assumption that the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math> is constant is not correct. It can be shown that</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>98</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>14</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>s</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Hence, the new model is given by</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>s</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>98</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>14</mn></msup></mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>s</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">When <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, it is known that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Suggest <strong>one</strong> improvement to the use of Euler’s method which might increase the accuracy of the prediction of the model.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Use a smaller step length&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>Use a better method such as Runge-Kutta&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>(Try to) solve the equation exactly&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[1 mark]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13922475","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.1ei","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Suggest one improvement to the use of Euler’s method which might increase the accuracy of the prediction of the model.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.18—Eulers method for 2nd order DEs","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
